description: 340 Brook St, #1, Westbrook, ME  3b/2B or use as 2B/2B and an office New (1year) construction Gorgeous townhouse at unbeatable location awaiting its residents! Available immediately.  Take the pride to live in this gorgeous and spacious duplex townhouse! Both units are identical mirror to each other, left or #1 is available. Conveniently located in quiet, serene residential area in Westbrook at the border with Falmouth, and Pride's corner, just minutes outside of Portland, close to I-95 and many restaurants and shops.  This large 1,400 sq. ft. , 2 level, 3B/2 Full baths condo with a plus 700 sq ft full basement in addition is in a Colonial style Duplex and offers loads of charm, light, and modern touches and features as Granite counter tops, beautiful Dartmouth Maple high kitchen cabinets with dovetailed drawers, modern light fixtures, brand new Stainless steel appliances, wood style bath tiles with adorable dark grey vanity cabinets, lovely hardwood floors, comfortable decks. Washer/Dryer Hookups in the basement, On demand water heater, ceiling light -fans in each bedroom; walk-in closets, and great size backyard space. Basement has an additional dog-house entrance in the back. Parking for 2 cars. An amazing property.  Residents will enjoy quiet airy surroundings offered by 1.6 acres lot behind the building with many mature trees and a great landscaping, while still finding all the necessities within easy reach -15 minutes from downtown Portland and 10 minutes from downtown Westbrook, minutes from Riverside Golf Course, Falmouth Spur, U.S. Route 302, 295, Turnpike Exit 53, UNE and IDEX. Steps from Sebago to Sea trail.   The rent is $1,930. Available 12/1/2019.  1 YEAR LEASE. Snow plowing, landscape and sewer are included. Residents are responsible for electricity, water, and very economic gas (propane) heat and HW.  No pets and Non-smokers only, sorry.  $35 non-refundable application fee per applicant. Phone interview required.  Rental Requirements- - 2 years of good rental history, homeowner or cosigner - Good credit and references - Proof of income - First rent and a 2 month rent security deposit   Please email with a brief description of your situation and a phone # to contact you. This stunning, fully-renovated home is now available for the first time ever as a vacation rental home. Also available for flexible 2020 winter leases. Winter lease rate from January thru end of March is $4975/mo plus utils if all three months (Jan, Feb, March) are rented. Shorter and Longer leases available at negotiated rates.   This Home is also available for short-term vacation leases with a 3-night minimum stay, 2 nights in the winter months.  Summer weeks priced at $8365/week with a 10-night minimum stay/minimum fee.   January weeks priced at $3475/week or $675/night.    This beautifully renovated home is located in the most popular area of Cape Elizabeth, popular because of the close proximity to downtown Portland and the stunning private neighborhood beach, the shops, restaurants and bakeries of Cottage Road and Willard Square, and an easy walk to the Portland headlight--the world's most photographed lighthouse.  This 2800 square foot home offers several large spaces for entertaining and smaller spaces for quiet moments--the best of both worlds. The layout is as follows:  First Floor:  *Huge chef's kitchen/great room/casual dining area, featuring casual lounge furniture from Maine Cottage, a dining table/chairs and a breakfast bar. Chef's dream of a kitchen features commercial grade 48" Viking stove with dual ovens, 2 Bosch dishwashers, 2 farmhouse sinks and a Sub-Zero Refrigerator. If your income is under $32,850 (1 person), $37,550 (2 people), $42,250 (3 people), or $46,900 (4 people), you may qualify for affordable housing. Affordable Housing Program APPLICATION REQUIREMENTS Applicants for residency must satisfy four criteria for approval: 1. INCOME: Rent may not exceed 40% of gross income. Rent plus monthly expenses may not exceed 50% of gross income. Income must be verifiable. 2. EMPLOYMENT: Stable employment of six months or longer with the current employer. If length of employment is less than six months, most recent prior employment will be considered, provided that it is in the same business or industry. If the applicant is retired or disabled and is otherwise able to document sufficient income to support rent, then employment is not required for approval. 3. RESIDENT HISTORY: Positive landlord references and/or mortgage payment history.4.ESTABLISHED CREDIT: Credit report must show positive payment history. Any of the following may result in denial of the application: historic delinquency, recent bankruptcy, unsatisfied judgments, collections or repossessions. do NOT contact me with unsolicited services or offers

Affordable Housing Program APPLICATION REQUIREMENTS Applicants for residency must satisfy four criteria for approval: 1. INCOME: Rent may not exceed 40% of gross income. Rent plus monthly expenses may not exceed 50% of gross income. Income must be verifiable. 2. EMPLOYMENT: Stable employment of six months or longer with the current employer. If length of employment is less than six months, most recent prior employment will be considered, provided that it is in the same business or industry. If the applicant is retired or disabled and is otherwise able to document sufficient income to support rent, employment is not required for approval. 3. RESIDENT HISTORY: Positive landlord references and/or mortgage payment history.4.ESTABLISHED CREDIT: Credit report must show positive payment history. Any of the following may result in denial of the application: historic delinquency, recent bankruptcy, unsatisfied judgments, collections or repossessions.

Affordability now comes with a view! IMPORTANT! Applicants must comply with the following: Affordable Housing waitlist for 1 bedroom apartments for $837/month or 2 bedroom apartments for $1000/month. If your income is under $32,850 (1 person), $37,550 (2 people), $42,250 (3 people), or $46,900 (4 people), you may qualify for affordable housing. Affordable Housing Program APPLICATION REQUIREMENTS Applicants for residency must satisfy four criteria for approval: 1. INCOME: Rent may not exceed 40% of gross income. Rent plus monthly expenses may not exceed 50% of gross income. Income must be verifiable. 2. EMPLOYMENT: Stable employment of six months or longer with the current employer. If length of employment is less than six months, most recent prior employment will be considered, provided that it is in the same business or industry. If the applicant is retired or disabled and is otherwise able to document sufficient income to support rent, employment is not required for approval. 3. RESIDENT HISTORY: Positive landlord references and/or mortgage payment history.4.ESTABLISHED CREDIT: Credit report must show positive payment history. Any of the following may result in denial of the application: historic delinquency, recent bankruptcy, unsatisfied judgments, collections or repossessions.

If your income is under $32,850 (1 person), $37,550 (2 people), $42,250 (3 people), or $46,900 (4 people), you may qualify for affordable housing. Affordable Housing Program APPLICATION REQUIREMENTS Applicants for residency must satisfy four criteria for approval: 1. INCOME: Rent may not exceed 40% of gross income. Rent plus monthly expenses may not exceed 50% of gross income. Income must be verifiable. 2. EMPLOYMENT: Stable employment of six months or longer with the current employer. If length of employment is less than six months, most recent prior employment will be considered, provided that it is in the same business or industry. If the applicant is retired or disabled and is otherwise able to document sufficient income to support rent, then employment is not required for approval. 3. RESIDENT HISTORY: Positive landlord references and/or mortgage payment history.4.ESTABLISHED CREDIT: Credit report must show positive payment history. Any of the following may result in denial of the application: historic delinquency, recent bankruptcy, unsatisfied judgments, collections or repossessions.

RESIDENT HISTORY: Positive landlord references and/or mortgage payment history.4.ESTABLISHED CREDIT: Credit report must show positive payment history.
